# claude — ignore everything in .claude/ EXCEPT .claude/skills/, which holds
# the portable AI procedure framework from PR #133 (docs/spec-portable-ai-procedures.md)
# and must ship in the repo. Note: gitignore can't re-include children of an
# excluded parent, so we exclude .claude/* (contents) rather than .claude/ (dir)
# and re-include .claude/skills/ explicitly.
.claude/*
!.claude/skills/
# checked-in shared permission rules (the /ship `gh pr merge` ask-gate, #353) — must ship in the
# repo, so re-include it explicitly past the `.claude/*` exclusion. Per-machine overrides live in
# .claude/settings.local.json, which stays ignored by the `.claude/*` rule above.
!.claude/settings.json
# per-machine Skill state (team-cache, etc.) — never commit
.claude/skills/**/.team-cache.json
# skill-creator generated run artifacts (Python bytecode, packaged .skill files) — never commit
.claude/skills/skill-creator/**/__pycache__/
.claude/skills/**/*.skill
.vercel

# agent scratch notes — emergent design decisions, working memory
.scratch/

# operator-script source data — contains member PII, never commit
scripts/*.csv

# Skill-eval workspaces (generated run artifacts; see docs plan-skill-evals-baseline)
.claude/skills/*-workspace/
